dc_title_s: O'Brien County, Iowa, 1954, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet label. Image is a photoreduction of the mosaic created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol BKK. Form of individual image numbering: BKK-1N-[number], or BKK-2N-[number]."Flying completed 11-2-54" Flown by Puckett Aerial Surveys, Inc. Jackson, Mississippi. "Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
